00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:43,900
prefer, where, you know, we will avoid the risk of being eliminated by occupying many

142
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,380
platforms in space.

143
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:46,800
It doesn't need to be another rock.

144
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,600
You know, we think about Mars.

145
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,840
Elon Musk thinks about Mars.

146
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:54,480
But that's just another residue of the formation of the solar system.

147
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,440
So we have the Earth as one rock.

148
00:09:56,440 --> 00:10:00,320
Then there is another one next to it, which is called Mars.

149
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,440
And this is just like being in the jungle.

150
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:07,360
You are sitting on one tree and you are saying, oh, here is another tree that I can move to.

151
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:13,520
To me, that's not very appealing, because we know that moving to a city that has a design,

152
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:17,940
artificial design, can provide a much better quality of life.

153
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:25,180
And so we could aspire to build a space platform that will host people and create a habitat

154
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:30,500
that is artificially designed instead of us relying on the nuclear fusion reactor that

155
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,080
the sun is.

156
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:38,980
We will create our nuclear fusion reactor on that habitat.

157
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:43,900
And so I think that would be a better approach for long-term survival.

158
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,060
But time will tell.

159
00:10:46,060 --> 00:10:47,060
Robin, your view?

160
00:10:47,060 --> 00:10:52,980
I completely agree that the key question here is to lay out sort of the distribution of

