00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:33,800
But it's important to think about the thick tail of the largest possibilities for our

169
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:38,720
future, because if there's a distribution of things like us out in the universe, we

170
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:44,080
can see so far that if it's a thick tail, most likely the median thing we see would

171
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:47,560
be in that thickest, that highest tail of the distribution.

172
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:52,880
That is, in history, the median person who died in a pandemic or war probably died in

173
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:58,080
nearly the largest pandemic or largest war ever because those things have such thick

174
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:03,360
tails. And probably if we see any evidence of aliens out there, they are probably in

175
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:08,200
the thick tail of the largest, most impactful aliens out there.

176
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:13,200
So I think we do want to think about if they could manage to survive and grow, just how

177
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:17,920
big might they get, how much energy might they use, how much might they change their

178
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:21,640
physical environment? That's the sort of thing to be looking for out there.

179
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:26,560
Even if it's very rare as a descendant of where we are, it still has disproportionate

